    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You can send out your sacred animals to serve as messengers or omens. You gain the following benefits.</p><p><strong>Ability Score Increase.</strong> Increase your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20.</p><p><strong>Animal Messenger.</strong> You always have the @UUID[Compendium.dnd5e.spells.Item.X8w9EzYLGc4vQ1H2]{Animal Messenger} spell prepared. You can cast the spell without expending a spell slot. Once you cast the spell in this way, you can't cast it in this way again until you finish a Short or Long Rest. You can also cast the spell using spell slots you have of the appropriate level. When you cast the spell in this way, the animal must be one of your sacred animals; if there are no such animals in range, the spell fails.</p>",
